```java
class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n < 1) return false;
        double log = Math.log(n) / Math.log(3);
        return log % 1 == 0;
    }
}
```

This solution works by calculating the logarithm base 3 of the given number. If the result is an integer, then the number is a power of three. The `Math.log` function gives the natural logarithm, so we use `Math.log(n) / Math.log(3)` to get the logarithm base 3. The `% 1 == 0` check ensures that the result is an integer. If the result is an integer, the number is a power of three; otherwise, it's not.

